{"overview":"This G-flat major piece unfolds in a clear ternary (ABA') design with a lyrical cantabile principal theme, its harmonic character defined by a rich flatward tonal world that moves through C-flat major and E-flat minor before dissolving into a ghostly enharmonic excursion to B minor in the recapitulation's final bars—the piece's most distinctive and startling moment. The language blends Romantic chromatic warmth (modal mixture, bVI/bVII inflections, diminished seventh sequences) with a luminous, introspective intimacy that culminates in a ppp coda of near-total harmonic stillness.","cross_piece_tags":["ternary","nocturne","lyrical","meditative","intimate","modal_mixture","enharmonic_modulation","chromatic_mediant"]}
